Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["STBenchmark", "ObjectName",ExpressionUUID->"f455aadf-c7a2-467d-b9ec-dec6a44edaea"],

Cell[BoxData[GridBox[{
   {Cell[TextData[{
     StyleBox["STBenchmark[]", "TI"],
     " \[LineSeparator]runs the benchmark suite defined in \
mgExamples/mgDiagrams.wl: a dependency check (see STDependencies[]) followed \
by the STIntegrate / STNIntegrate cases exercising the supported input forms \
and backends. Cases run sequentially in the main kernel; caches are cleared \
between cases so that one case's state cannot poison the next. The file ships \
two splits \\[LongDash] \"Short\" (10 cases, default, ~smoke test) and \"Long\
\" (21 cases, developer regression coverage); pick between them with the \
\"Suite\" option."
    }], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"f1a518f3-b5a1-419f-9a76-3ddef9b8ea1b"]},
   {Cell[TextData[{
     StyleBox["STBenchmark[selector]", "TI"],
     " \[LineSeparator]restricts the run to a subset (e.g. \"diagrams\", \
{\"nIntDiagrams\", 1 ;; 3}, or a list of case ids). Options: \"Suite\" -> \
\"Short\" | \"Long\" (which case list to load); \"Verify\" -> True | False \
(cross-check nIntDiagrams via STVerify); \"Display\" -> \"Stream\" | \"Silent\
\"; \"Baseline\" -> Automatic | None | _String (path to baseline JSON); \
\"UpdateBaseline\" -> True | False | Automatic (bake current run as the new \
baseline; Automatic writes only when no baseline exists yet); \"Report\" -> \
None | _String (write a Markdown report); \"SkipPackageCheck\" -> True | \
False. Returns Null; per-case details are stored in $STLastBenchmarkResults \
(a list of Associations) for programmatic access."
    }], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"7367cbd3-d323-4143-a6d6-2083524de4e8"]}
  },
  GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Left}}},
  GridBoxItemSize->{
   "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}}]], "Usage",
 CellID->1,ExpressionUUID->"a15b7e60-652c-4253-aa32-b0163b14e11c"]
}, Open  ]],

